text: James Estabrook (September 4, 1796 – May 16, 1874) was a Worcester, Massachusetts grocer who served as the sheriff of Worcester County, Massachusetts from 1851 to 1853. ==Early life== Estabrook was born to James and Betsey (Lovell) Estabrook in Holden, Massachusetts, on September 4, 1796. ==References== Category:19th-century American people Category:1796 births Category:1874 deaths Category:Businesspeople from Boston Category:People from Holden, Massachusetts Category:People from Boston Category:People from Worcester, Massachusetts Category:Massachusetts Democrats Category:Massachusetts sheriffs Category:Massachusetts city council members
